        [
          "Camarilla \"Shovelhead\" - A painful reminder of a failed tactic that refuses to let it happen again. (V:tM Hard Mode)",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Logan Boese"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Solomon/Sarah  - A Caitiff from “Somewhere on the Eastern Seaboard”. A police officer in life, They were embraced in the early nineties, during a vicious war between the Sabbat and Camarilla. Specifically, they were embraced and dominated to serve as Cannon Fodder, to act as little more than a speed bump and diversionary tactic to the invading sabbat. Their sire was killed before they managed to flee the city, and the new Caitiff found themselves free to abandon the doomed defense. Returning to their family after that proved… Unfortunate. Whether they were not accepted or had a more tragic turn to that event is in the past now, but what is relevant to the moment is that it turned them loose upon their new world, and they have wandered the country, seeking anything that reminds them of their mortal life. Nominally, they are Camarilla, but only because of the horrors they’ve personally seen the Sabbat unleash. They'll do whatever they can to fight the Sabbat whenever and wherever they’re found, and they can never be convinced that they’re gone. Even the lawlessness of the Anarchs holds no appeal to them, as keeper of peace and order. In the meantime, they’ll settle for letting those pricks in the Camarilla know that they’re not happy about the way their kind are treated, and will make it a point to be at any meetings or elysium they can to ensure that nothing like what happens to them ever happens again. They want nothing more than to voice just how angry they are at the Camarilla."
        ],
        [
